{
  "level": "Essential Grammar in Use",
  "part": "Unit 11",
  "tree": {
    "id": "root",
    "text": "How long have you (been) ... ? (延续性状态与动作表达)",
    "emoji": "⏳",
    "state": "emoji",
    "children": [
      {
        "id": "present_vs_perfect",
        "text": "Present vs Present Perfect (一般现在时与现在完成时对比)",
        "emoji": "⚖️",
        "state": "hidden",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "state_continues",
            "text": "Present perfect: started in past and still continues (动作/状态始于过去且延续至今)",
            "emoji": "➡️",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "no_present_duration",
            "text": "Do not use present simple for duration/since/for (不能用一般现在时表达延续的动作/状态)",
            "emoji": "🚫",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "how_long_usage",
        "text": "How Long, For, & Since (询问与表达时长)",
        "emoji": "📏",
        "state": "hidden",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "continuous_pref",
            "text": "Continuous is more usual for action verbs (动作动词通常用完成进行时)",
            "emoji": "🔄",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "state_verbs_simple",
            "text": "State verbs (know, like, have...) must use simple (状态动词只能用完成简单时)",
            "emoji": "🧩",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "live_work",
        "text": "Verbs: Live & Work (居住与工作)",
        "emoji": "🏠",
        "state": "hidden",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "both_correct",
            "text": "Either continuous or simple is correct (用进行时或简单时皆可)",
            "emoji": "✅",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "always_simple",
            "text": "Always use simple with 'always' (有 always 时必须使用简单时)",
            "emoji": "⚠️",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "negatives_since_for",
        "text": "Negatives with Since/For (否定句中用完成简单时)",
        "emoji": "❌",
        "state": "hidden",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "simple_neg",
            "text": "Use present perfect simple: haven't seen / phoned... (表示“多久没做某事”时用简单时)",
            "emoji": "🗣️",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "examples",
        "text": "Key Examples (重点例句)",
        "emoji": "💡",
        "state": "hidden",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "ex1",
            "text": "They have been married for 20 years. (他们结婚20年了 - 不能用 are married)",
            "emoji": "💍",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "ex2",
            "text": "How long have you known Jane? (你认识简多久了？ - 不能用 known 的进行时)",
            "emoji": "🤝",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "ex3",
            "text": "I've always lived in the country. (我一直住在乡下 - 有 always 用 lived)",
            "emoji": "🌾",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "ex4",
            "text": "I haven't seen Tom since Monday. (周一以来我一直没见过汤姆 - 否定句用 haven't seen)",
            "emoji": "📅",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
